We didn’t realise it was so tough for our dedicated and hard-working members of parliament. According to outgoing Economic Freedom Fighters MP Godrich Gardee, the R1.1 million-a-year salary – and numerous perks – are not nearly enough to keep body and soul together, never mind compensate these selfless people for their service. As he resigned from the House of Assembly to go into a private law practice, Gardee complained that his salary was “disgusting”. He said he could understand why some parliamentarians took backhanders from organisations like Bosasa. He didn’t go into much detail on MPs’ benefits, which include 88...